parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Sudden acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, and property damage.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
the accelerator pedal becomes stuck or jammed
the vehicle surges forward without warning
the brakes are unable to overcome the acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Spare Tire Failure (Firestone Radial Special Spare)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the spare tire can lead to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially if it occurs while the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The tire belt or tread detaches from the tire
the spare tire explodes while in storage
steel belts protrude from the tire
the tire is no longer usable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump relay can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to unexpected loss of power and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle does not start right away
erratic stalling at different speeds
difficulty starting the engine
engine stalling while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the driver to run out of fuel, leading to unexpected stops and potential accidents.
symptoms: The gas gauge gives false readings
the gas gauge is inaccurate
the gas gauge is stuck on a certain level
the vehicle runs out of fuel unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine stalling can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or navigating intersections.
symptoms: The engine cuts off without warning
the vehicle stalls while driving at various speeds
the vehicle stalls when coming to a stop sign.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Radiator Failure Leading to Engine Damage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The radiator failure can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage or failure, which can result in costly repairs and potentially cause accidents due to loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The engine overheats
the radiator leaks coolant
the vehicle loses power or stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Electrical System Failure Leading to Vehicle Fires
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An electrical system failure can cause a vehicle to catch fire, resulting in total loss of the vehicle and potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Vehicle catches fire while parked
no apparent reason for the fire
fire inspector determines the fire is electrical-related.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Stalling or Engine Cut-Off at Low Speeds
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or cutting off at low speeds can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Engine cuts off at 45-50 miles per hour while driving
requiring the driver to wait before restarting the vehicle.
